Commands For TS setup:

1. Create a Folder, and open it in VSCode
2. npm i typescript -g
3. tsc –init
4. npm i nodemon
5. Add main.ts in that folder
6. Add start script in package.json: “start”: “nodemon main.js”
7. npx tsc main –w (For recompiling .ts -> .js everytime on Save)
8. npm start (“start”: “nodemon main.js”; For running .js file everytime on Save)

Ragav:
Create a Typescript folder:

npm init -y
npm install typescript -- install typescript only for this folder
npx tsc -v

then create a test folder under node_modules folder. note: I created this note file

create basics.js file and run it using npx basics.js.
basics.js file will be generated and then run
node basics.js

add export to the top of basics.ts
